==German==
===Etymology===
Probably influenced by ''[[schnicken]]'' "to flip one's fingers" and ''[[Schnickschnack]]'' (from ''[[schnacken]]'' Northern German for "to [[chat]]"). In English sometimes called [[Schnick Schnak Schnuk]].

===Idiom===
'''Schnick Schnack Schnuck'''
# the game of ''rock, paper, scissors''
